      • FIXED_MAX_KEY_VALUE_SIZE_CAP

        private static final int FIXED_MAX_KEY_VALUE_SIZE_CAP
        This is the fixed key value size cap in 4.0 and it is based on OffloadStoreImpl.keyValueSizeCapFromPageSize(int) with pageSize=8192. In 4.2 the possibility to have larger page cache pages was introduced, but we still want to keep the same key value size cap for simplicity.

      • splitPosInLeaf

        private int splitPosInLeaf​(PageCursor cursor,
                           int insertPos,
                           KEY newKey,
                           VALUE newValue,
                           int keyCountAfterInsert,
                           double ratioToKeepInLeftOnSplit)
        Calculates a valid and as optimal as possible position where to split a leaf if inserting a key overflows, trying to come as close as possible to ratioToKeepInLeftOnSplit. There are a couple of goals/conditions which drives the search for it:
        • The returned position will be one where the keys ending up in the left and right leaves respectively are guaranteed to fit.
        • Out of those possible positions the one will be selected which leaves left node filled with with space closest to "targetLeftSpace".
        We loop over an imaginary range of keys where newKey has already been inserted at insertPos in the current node. splitPos point to position in the imaginary range while currentPos point to the node. In the loop we "move" splitPos from left to right, accumulating space for left node as we go and calculate delta towards targetLeftSpace. We want to continue loop as long as:
        • We are still moving closer to optimal divide (currentDelta < prevDelta) and
        • We are still inside end of range (splitPost < keyCountAfterInsert) and
        • We have not accumulated to much space to fit in left node (accumulatedLeftSpace <= totalSpace).
        But we also have to force loop to continue if the current position does not give a possible divide because right node will be given to much data to fit (!thisPosPossible). Exiting loop means we've gone too far and thus we move one step back after loop, but only if the previous position gave us a possible divide.
        Parameters:
        cursor - PageCursor to use for reading sizes of existing entries.
        insertPos - the pos which the new key will be inserted at.
        newKey - key to be inserted.
        newValue - value to be inserted.
        keyCountAfterInsert - key count including the new key.
        ratioToKeepInLeftOnSplit - What ratio of keys to try and keep in left node, 1=keep as much as possible, 0=move as much as possible to right
        Returns:
        the pos where to split.
